  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI acceptance; however, the supporting validation activity that generated the primary ValidationResult was conducted as a high-fidelity numerical simulation. The narrative characterises the simulation as functionally equivalent to a bench experiment given the controlled boundary conditions and published mesh-independence data, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', creating an inference-method mismatch against the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'experimental-validation'. Decision is recorded as Accepted based on the narrative argument, masking the structural break.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/hemolysis-experimental-validation",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
