    "name": "Hemolysis QoI verification must use experimental validation",
    "description": "For Class III VAD devices at MRL 5, acceptance of hemolysis index predictions as the primary QoI requires that the supporting evidence be generated through experimental-validation activities. Bench or in-vitro experimental data must form the evidentiary basis for the ValidationResult used to close this requirement. Computational surrogates are not a recognised substitute under this requirement.",
    "requiredVerificationMethod": "experimental-validation"
  },
