    "type": "Activity",
    "name": "High-fidelity CFD hemolysis simulation — MRL 5 operating envelope",
    "description": "A fully resolved LES simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump was executed across all 5 flow-speed operating points. Mesh independence was confirmed at 12 million cells. The simulation incorporated the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model with Monte Carlo sampling over 500 realisations of inlet boundary conditions and blood viscosity. The team argued that the controlled, deterministic boundary conditions and published experimental geometry data render this simulation 'equivalent to a controlled bench experiment' for the purposes of hemolysis threshold assessment.",
    "activityType": "numerical-simulation"
  },
