    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the high-fidelity LES simulation with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification provides evidence of hemolysis index values below the absolute clinical threshold across all five operating points. The team's narrative argument holds that the controlled boundary conditions, mesh-independence confirmation, and published geometry data render the simulation functionally equivalent to a controlled in-vitro experiment, satisfying the intent of the experimental-validation requirement. This narrative argument is recorded here; however, the structured activityType of the supporting Activity is 'numerical-simulation', which does not match the requiredVerificationMethod 'experimental-validation' declared in the governing Requirement, constituting an unresolved inference-method mismatch under W-AR-03.",
